    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-19T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="406"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Indonesia/12–1749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d406fn1">Repeated as 632 to Batavia.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-19T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 19, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>644, <gloss target="#t_reurtels1">Reurtel</gloss> No. 1443, Dec 17,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d406fn2">Not printed; it gave the text of the Indonesian invitation
                        to attend ceremonies at Jakarta (Batavia), December 27–28.</note> please
                    advise Palar orally that the US Govt appreciates invitation send delegation
                    attend celebration transfer of sovereignty to Repub of US of Indonesia, and
                    accepts invitation, designating Mr. Jacob Beam, US <gloss target="#t_ConGen1"
                        >ConGen</gloss>, Batavia, as <gloss target="#t_Rep1">Rep</gloss> of U.S.
                    Govt. All arrangements re US Representation and transportation of <gloss
                        target="#t_Rep1">Rep</gloss>s will be made thru office of US GonGen,
                    Batavia.</p>
                <p>Please confirm orally Mr. Cochran’s appreciation and acceptance of invitation to
                    be present ceremonies, explaining that Mr. Cochran will attend as U.S. <gloss
                        target="#t_Rep1">Rep</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_UNCFIN1">UNCFI</gloss>. Mr. Cochran leaving NY Dec 21 by plane
                    for Batavia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
